---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cover Letter" activeTab="cover-letter">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Cover Letter</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Graduate Application</p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-white p-12 md:p-20 shadow-xl font-neue text-slate-800 leading-relaxed space-y-12">
        </div>
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start border-b border-slate-100 pb-8">
            <div class="space-y-1">
                <p class="font-black uppercase text-xl text-industrial-black">Dylan Purbrick</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Mo. 0451 317 463</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Ultimo, NSW 2007</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-500">10/03/2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <p class="font-black uppercase text-industrial-black tracking-tight underline underline-offset-8">RE: GRADUATE ENGINEER PROGRAM APPLICATION</p>
            <p>Dear Hiring Manager,</p>
            <p>I am writing to apply for the Graduate Engineer Program at Industrus Engineering. I am currently finishing my final year of a Bachelor of Engineering (Honours) in Mechatronic Engineering at UTS while working as an Engineering Assistant at Keith Engineering. My professional journey is driven by a deep passion for mechanical systems and a belief that the best learning happens through hands-on experience. I am excited by the prospect of rotating through your project roles to apply my technical skills to real-world challenges</p>

            <p>A commitment to ethical conduct and the highest standards of professional accountability<br>
                At Keith Engineering, I am often responsible for the final quality check of manufacturing drawings before they reach the fitting shop. My task is to ensure every detail is technically accurate to prevent material waste or mechanical failure. I systematically cross-reference every CAD model against its Bill of Materials (BOM) to catch discrepancies early. By identifying and documenting errors before production, I’ve helped maintain the company’s reputation for reliability. This process has taught me that accountability isn't just about finishing a task, but about ensuring the final product is safe and efficient.
            </p>

            <p>Demonstrated ability to effectively communicate both with other engineers and with stakeholders from different <br>
                fields. My role at Keith Engineering requires me to act as a bridge between our technical drafting team and our clients. I am tasked with taking technical site visit reports and summarizing them into clear project costs and customer quotes. I translate complex engineering data into accessible information so that clients understand exactly what they are paying for. As a result, our internal teams can work faster, and our customers feel more confident in our process. This experience has refined my ability to communicate technical ideas to people from a variety of backgrounds.
            </p>
            
            <p>The ability to engage with a creative, innovative and proactive environment <br>
                For a university project, I set out to design a functional, print-in-place set of pliers using additive manufacturing. The challenge was to create a tool with moving parts that required no assembly or post-processing. I proactively used overlapping CAD geometry and tight tolerance control to ensure the rotational joint moved smoothly right off the print bed. The final tool achieved full marks and proved that I can think creatively to solve mechanical constraints. This project highlighted my drive to push the boundaries of what a single manufacturing process can achieve.
            </p>

            <p>Demonstrated ability to use and manage information.<br>
                I recently developed a ROS 2 perception subsystem for an autonomous robot designed to recognize artwork. My goal was to create a system that could process live camera data and match it to a digital library of images in real-time. I implemented an OpenCV algorithm to manage the high volume of visual data and return accurate results with a confidence score. The system achieved a 90% success rate during physical testing. Managing this complex data pipeline was essential for the robot to successfully interact with its environment
            </p>

                        <p>The ability to manage your own performance in a professional environment.<br>
                I have spent the last few years balancing a rigorous engineering degree with two distinct roles: an Engineering Assistant and a Shift Supervisor. This requires me to switch quickly between technical CAD modeling and high-pressure team management in a hospitality setting. I manage my own schedule to ensure that I never miss a deadline at work or a milestone in my studies. This self-reliance has taught me how to stay organized and deliver results even when under significant pressure. I am comfortable taking ownership of my performance and constantly looking for ways to improve.
            </p>

            <p>A demonstrated ability to work as part of a team and to show leadership when required.<br>
                As a co-founder and Team Executive of the UTS MechSoc, I helped grow a society focused on professional development for engineering students. I was responsible for overseeing our executive team and organizing large-scale events, such as a multi-day trip for 30 people. I focused on delegating tasks clearly and keeping the team motivated throughout the planning process. Successfully executing these events reinforced my belief that a team performs best when everyone understands their role and feels supported. I am eager to bring this collaborative mindset to the teams at Industrus
            </p>

            </div>

            <p>I would appreciate the change to discuss how my hands on background can contribute to Industrus Engieneering’s future projects. I prefer to be contacted via email at Dylan.m.Purbrick@gmail.com and by mobile at (+61) 451 317 463. Thank you again for taking the time to consider, I look forward to hearing from you.</p>
            <p>Best Regards,<br/><span class="font-black uppercase text-xl">Dylan Purbrick</span></p>


        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
